noun.description: A young saithe or coalfish, Pollachius virens.

verb.description: To have or cause a pricking sensation, like the feeling of pins and needles; to prickle, tingle. Scottish.
To twinkle, sparkle. Chiefly Scottish and English regional.

origin: Mid 19th century; earliest use found in Peter Buchan (1790–1854), folk-song collector, historian, and publisher. Origin unknown<br>early 18th century; earliest use found in John Kelly (c1684–1751), writer. Probably a variant of prickle with infixed -n-; compare later pringle.
